    "Typically, ALARP provides the following risk tolerance ranges (Hurst et al., 2019):",
    "Although the transposition into EU law of ALARP is limited 12 and controversial 13, AIA's risk categories overlap with the tolerance ranges shown in Fig. 1.",
    "14 These risk categories can be summarised as follows.",
    "15 Unacceptable risk includes (AIA, Title II):",
    "• AIs that may cause significant harm through (a) subliminal manipulation of individuals' consciousness that distorts their behaviour 16 or (b) exploitation of vulnerabilities-age, physical or mental disability-of a specific group of people that distorts the behaviour of its members."
